Installtion and configartion of a home lab potainer 

1. Update the system
bash
sudo apt update
sudo apt upgrade -y
sudo reboot
2. Install Docker
After reboot:

bash
curl -fsSL https://get.docker.com | sh
sudo systemctl enable docker
sudo systemctl start docker
sudo usermod -aG docker $USER
sudo reboot
Docker is now installed and enabled as a service.
3. Install Portainer
After the second reboot, log in again and run:

bash
sudo docker volume create portainer_data

sudo docker run -d \
  -p 9443:9443 \
  --name portainer \
  --restart=always \
  -v /var/run/docker.sock:/var/run/docker.sock \
  -v portainer_data:/data \
  portainer/portainer-ce:latest
This pulls Portainer and starts it as a container.

4. Access your home lab UI
On the Pi, find its IP:

bash
hostname -I
From your laptop/PC, open in a browser:

text
https://PI_IP:9443
